{
  "stem": "19895.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 96.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "During the time as I was in high school, I was aware that there were Zionist activities within the school-- very minimal, very minimal.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Our school principal and teachers were not in favor of that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I kind of reflected that a little bit, that they didn't want us to stand up for ourselves.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They want us to survive kind of quietly and not to fight.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they thought that that's the approach you might survive.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "On the other hand, according some, it was a mistake.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because a tremendous number of our class perished as well as tremendous number of the Jewish population perished.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But I am not aware of people who were able to get out of the country, although it's known and documented that there were very few, but some.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "How did they teach us not to be fighting?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "By not teaching us to stand up and fight, except we knew for one or two of the teachers who had, who had different views who a little bit spoke of, of the days when, when Jews can have dignity again.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it was not the school's curricula to, to make us standing up for ourself as Jews, just fit in.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What were the struggles?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Struggles and conflicts-- well, I had plenty.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because as a young boy growing up, I could never understand what was my sin.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "What's wrong with somebody who is Jewish?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I, I had classmates in the elementary school who were, who were Catholics, who were Protestants.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And, and I was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I kind of understood that there are other religions.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But mine was singled out to be the wrong one.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And as, as I grew up, that always gave me a, a lot of questions in my mind about what and why people are anti-Semitic.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
